Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speaker recognition using audio data, which falls under the sound category.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses neural network models for speaker recognition, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computation and language category.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new training framework for neural networks to improve speaker recognition performance, which falls under the machine learning category.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper focuses on audio data, the proposed method can also be applied to visual data for speaker recognition, which falls under the computer vision and pattern recognition category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning techniques to improve speaker recognition performance, which falls under the artificial intelligence category.
